## Patent License

The licensor grants you a patent license for the software that covers
patent claims the licensor can license, or becomes able to license,
that you would infringe by using the software in the form provided by
the licensor, for any permitted purpose. If you file a lawsuit
against anyone for patent infringement related to any part of the
software, including changes and new works, your patent license to
the software ends immediately.

## Permitted Purposes

The permitted purposes are limited to use:

1. by any individual, business, or other organization with no more
   than 100 total individuals working as employees and independent
   contractors for the organization at any time during a calendar
   year, and

2. that does not result, directly or indirectly, in revenue greater
   than $1,000,000 (US) per calendar year, or the equivalent value in
   any other currency, from:

   - product sales to others;
   - service fees from others;
   - donations from others;
   - investment from others;
   - lending from others; and
   - revenue of any kind from selling or offering the software.

