## Definitions

The **licensor** is the individual or entity offering these terms,
and the **software** is the software the licensor makes available
under these terms.

**You** refers to the individual or entity agreeing to these terms.

**Your company** is any legal entity, sole proprietorship, or other
kind of organization that you work for, plus all organizations that
have control over, are under the control of, or are under common
control with that organization. **Control** means ownership of
substantially all the assets of an entity, or the power to direct its
management and policies by vote, contract, or otherwise. Control can
be direct or indirect.

**Your licenses** are all the licenses granted to you for the
software under these terms.

**Use** means anything you do with the software requiring one of your
licenses.

============================================================================
B. ADDITIONAL RESTRICTION — Narrowed Permitted Purposes
============================================================================

The rights holder narrows section "Permitted Purposes" of the base
license. For the purposes of this distribution, paragraphs (1) and
(2) of "Permitted Purposes" are REPLACED with the following, more
restrictive thresholds:

  1. Use by any individual, business, or other organization with no
     more than ONE (1) total individual working as an employee or
     independent contractor for the organization at any time during a
     calendar year (the original threshold of 100 is reduced to 1).

  2. Use that does not result, directly or indirectly, in revenue
     greater than THIRTY THOUSAND US DOLLARS ($30,000 USD) per
     calendar year, or the equivalent value in any other currency,
     from the sources listed in the base license (the original
     threshold of $1,000,000 USD is reduced to $30,000 USD).

Both conditions must be satisfied for the free license to apply. Use
that fails either condition is NOT a permitted purpose under these
terms and requires a separate written license from the rights holder.

All other terms of the base license — including its definitions,
warranty disclaimer, and patent provisions — continue to apply
unchanged.

This Additional Restriction does not modify the canonical text of the
base license; it only narrows the scope of the rights holder's free
permission.

